# ── Claude Code / agent session state (machine-local, never tracked) ──────────
.claude/
.claude.*

# ── Third-party acquired repositories (reference-only; consult by name) ───────
# External repos present on disk for reference by name only, per CLAUDE.md.
# Never tracked in this repo: no gitlinks, no paths, no submodules.
# claude-skills/ carries its own .git; tracking it as a gitlink would produce a
# broken embedded-repo reference with no .gitmodules. Gitignoring is the correct,
# non-destructive way to keep it on disk for reference only.
claude-skills/

# ── OS / editor junk ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.tmp

# ── Stack-agnostic build artifacts knowingly ignored ─────────────────────────
# Kept broad so this file stays valid regardless of the stack chosen after the
# C4 spike. Prune to the selected stack once one is chosen.
node_modules/
dist/
build/
out/
target/
bin/
*.o
*.a
*.class
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Large evidence binaries (per lab/EVIDENCE_INDEX.md) ──────────────────────
# Hashes are identity; paths are location. Manifests, logs, redacted tokens,
# and config snapshots ARE tracked in git. Large binary captures are NOT — they
# belong in Git LFS or an external artifact store, referenced by hash from the
# (tracked) manifest.
*.pcap
*.pcapng
*.mp4
*.mov
*.mkv
*.sig
*.gpg
*.age
